==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Electrometer
<hw>E`lec*trom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Electro-</ets> + <ets>-meter</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧lectrom⟦egrave⟧tre</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld>
<def>An instrument for measuring the quantity or intensity of
electricity; also, sometimes, and less properly, applied to an
instrument which indicates the presence of electricity (usually called
an <xex>electroscope</xex>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Balance electrometer</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Balance</er>.</cd></cs></p>

<p><ent>Electro-metrical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Electro-metric</ent>⟦br⟧
